The paper deals with facial expression recognition, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves a novel Region Attention Network (RAN), which is a deep learning architecture, indicating that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of facial expression datasets, which suggests that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Lastly, the paper discusses the real-world scenarios of facial expression recognition, which may involve human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
